                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.38/296: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-24T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 24, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. My number 37, March 23, 11 p.m. In further explanation of the Haitian
                    Government’s ideas both the “necessary protective works” and the “air base” in
                    the region of Gonaives would be as much or as little as we desired. The main
                    thing apparently is that the Haitian Government desires American naval or
                    military establishment of some sort in the country. This would complement and
                    give added strength and emphasis to the virtual naval base which we now have at
                    Gonaives by virtue of the arrangement whereby we simply notify time of the
                    arrival of warships, rather than ask permission for their presence in Haitian
                    waters. My own idea would be that these “necessary protective works” and the
                    “air base” should be initiated on a small scale, capable of whatever development
                    experience or international politics might indicate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
